# Euclid Example: Sets and Logic

## Set Relations

- Membership: `$element_of(x, A)$`
- Subset: `$subseteq(A, B)$`
- Difference: `$set_diff(A, B)$`
- Number sets: `$subset(NATURALS, INTEGERS) AND subset(INTEGERS, REALS)$`

## Logical Structure

- Infix logic: `$p AND q = r$`
- Implication: `$implies(p, q)$`
- Quantifiers: `$forall(x, implies(element_of(x, A), element_of(x, B)))$`

## Proof Notation

- Conclusion markers: `$therefore p$`
- Direction arrows: `$x mapsto x^2$`
